ringbolt
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a non-paid trip on a ship aided by one or more of the crew;a clandestine passage aided by one or more of the crew;(used by shipgirls, escapees, etc.) [?f. a play on ring `vagina; anus' and bolt `run for it'; or from a play on ringbolt cf Golden rivet; or mere elaboration on bolt




Origin:
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes:
